Sentencas: A non-close-packed (NCP) silica opal connected by cylindrical rods was prepared using a selective etching technique.
Titulo: High thermal stability of three-dimensionally ordered nano-composite cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Using sol-gel impregnation of the NCP silica opal template, La0.8Sr0.2MnO3/Zr0.84Y0.16O2 (LSM/YSZ) composite cathodes were fabricated for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: High thermal stability of three-dimensionally ordered nano-composite cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The microstructure of the as-prepared cathode revealed three-dimensionally (3D) ordered hollow spheres connected by cylindrical tubes.
Titulo: High thermal stability of three-dimensionally ordered nano-composite cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Even after high-temperature sintering at 1000 degrees C, the 3D ordered nano-network remained stable.
Titulo: High thermal stability of three-dimensionally ordered nano-composite cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy was used to study the oxygen reduction reaction kinetics of the 3D ordered LSM/YSZ electrode.
Titulo: High thermal stability of three-dimensionally ordered nano-composite cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The impedance behavior was similar to that of a mixed ionic-electronic conductor, different from the behavior of traditional micro-scaled LSM/YSZ electrodes.
Titulo: High thermal stability of three-dimensionally ordered nano-composite cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The nanometer-scale particle size and continuous nano-network are the main reasons for this divergence in behavior.
Titulo: High thermal stability of three-dimensionally ordered nano-composite cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells
